@node Localization "Localization"

LazyMines is localized, so if you have v2.1 or higher of the OS LazyMines will
try to use the language you have set in Preferences. If there is no catalog for
your language, English will be used as default.

Since I'm not very good at languages I've only written one additional catalog
(the Swedish one). However I've included some files so that you easily can make
LazyMines support your language too. Read @{"Instructions" link Catalogs/instructions/main} in the Catalog directory
for more information.

@endnode
